				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Great spell.  I always keep it up during combat.  The extra ac has prob saved my life many times.  The healing affect is nice when solo.  I understand that there is a cost issue with some people.  Here's how to weigh out the cost issue:<BR>
Would you rather spend a few plat or go on a corpse run?  Personally I would preffer to spend the plat.  Each cast costs about 4gp and lasts about 1 hour.  So for 9.6pp you can get 24 hours of coverage.  I don't know how much money anyone else makes but I make enough that I don't even notice the loss of 9.6pp/24hours.  <BR>
<BR>
Boring example---&gt;<BR>
If I kill Golras for 4 hours I will make like 28pp.  I have done lots of Golra studies and average loot off of a Golra is 6gp (I averaged it out over the course of 100 kills and didnt include copper or loot that you sell for cash) and on the average I kill one every 5 minutes (respawn rate is 10 minutes but I pull multiple camps).  To keep the shield on for those 4 hours it would cost approx 1.6pp or 6% of the loot.  During those 4 hours the Golra will take about a million swings at me from either agro or my pet dying and the only way to recover the health lost from those swings is the regen from this spell.<BR>
