				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(10,145102);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >10</font></a></b>
				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Shimmering Orb, a 350PP item, adds 15 AC and 25 HP. This spell adds 15AC and HP regen. When you balance out the 5gp cost of each cast, that means that in 700 casts of this spell, you equal what you would have paid for the shimmering orb. I think that sounds like a great deal to me! As for PP being a problem, well, that's because you are soloing too much, my friends. groups in dungeons will net you about 5 to 10 pp per hour, easy. If you are smart and watch for deals at the bazaar, you can resell items at 50 to 100pp profit. Work drops in dungeons for other resale. There should be no reason, after you get to level 24, that you should have to worry about money anymore. Unless you hunt nothing but blues all the time. I am in a guild populated mostly by Barb Shaman and Warriors, adn each of them envy the abilities and strengths of the Mage class, even over what a Necro can do. Level 36 warriors are amazed buy the damage a little 27th mage can dish out. We become one of the more important casters in a group support role, not only with our DD and portable tanks (pets), but our damage sheilds, weapon summons, food, water, etc, well, those can be invaluable during a long dungeon session. If you have stuck with your mage this far, and discounted the calss bashing of those who don't have the intelligence to work a mage, then good for you. You have definately made the right choice!<BR>
<BR>
-------------<BR>
Korrso Nocturnus<BR>
27th Level Magi<BR>
The Bears of Oboo on Lanys T'Vyl
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
