			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Xvar,<BR>
<BR>
400pp for 5 stones?  What stones were you purchasing??!!<BR>
<BR>
Now, with that over... AC buff for any caster is like giving a newbie Valor.  Casters have an AC of like 4 and 10 hitpoints to match.  I, myself, am always guild grouped so I just kinda hang out in the back and cast on the critters.  Sometimes (ok, a lot of the time) I get wailed on, sometimes I don't; but at all times I need as many AC buffs as possible.  If a caster (with the AC of 4) gets hit we get hit for 20-60 dmg (As I am sure you have all experienced).  With the phantom chain I only get hit for the high teens and low 20's.  I guess my point is that though it only adds 10-15 to the AC, it dramatically increases our life expectancy.  =)<BR>
<BR>
Oh... and though I am not *BROKE*, I count my copper pieces too.  =)  <BR>
<BR>
Hunt Well and Be Safe, all!<BR>
<BR>
Beldanne Eltieviel, Magician of the 29th Circle<BR>
Deus ex Militi<BR>
Mithanial Marr
